  "local_port": 37292,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I upload a picture to my little bitty picture window on Quora?",
  "response": "To upload or change your profile picture on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log into your Quora Account**: Open your web browser, navigate to the Quora website, and log into your account if you haven't already.\n\n2. **Go to Your Profile**: Click on your name or profile picture in the top-right corner of the screen to access your profile page.\n\n3. **Edit Profile**: On your profile page, you'll see an \"Edit\" button next to your profile picture. Click on it.\n\n4. **Change Picture**: In the edit window, you'll find an option to change your photo. This might be a camera icon or a link like \"Change Photo.\" Click on it.\n\n5. **Upload Image**: A file dialog will open, allowing you to select an image file from your computer. Choose the picture you wish to upload.\n\n6. **Adjust and Save**: Once you've selected your image, you may have options to crop or adjust it. Make any adjustments if prompted, then save your changes.\n\n7. **Check**: Ensure that your new profile picture appears correctly on your profile.\n\nIf you're using the Quora mobile app, the steps are similar, but the interface might vary slightly:\n\n1. **Open the App** and log in if necessary.\n\n2. **Go to Your Profile**: Tap on your profile picture or the menu icon (three horizontal lines) and then tap on your name or profile picture.\n\n3. **Edit Profile**: Look for an \"Edit\" or pencil icon near your profile picture and tap on it.\n\n4. **Change Photo**: Tap on your current profile picture and select the option to upload a new photo.\n\n5. **Select Image**: Choose the image from your phone's gallery or take a new one if the option is available.\n\n6. **Adjust and Save** your new profile picture.\n\nRemember that profile pictures on Quora should adhere to their community guidelines, so avoid inappropriate content.",
